******
[2] Thailand (Nakhon Ratchasima): H1N1
Date: Wed 20 Jun 2012
Source: Malaysian National News Agency (Bernama) [edited]
http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v6/newsworld.php?id=674416


The Ministry of Public Health reported Wednesday [20 Jun 2012] that 41 people have been confirmed as being infected with H1N1 influenza in northeastern Nakhon Ratchasima province since early June [2012].

Public Health Ministry Inspector General Kamron Chaisiri said 6 female and 35 male patients, including 6 hospital staff, have been admitted to Nakhon Ratchasima Rajanagarindra Psychiatric Hospital. The Xinhua news agency says initial investigation showed that the 1st flu victim was reported on 12 Jun 2012.

Kamron said all patients were given antiviral flu [medication?] and none of them is in critical condition. The hospital, however, has stopped admitting new patients until the situation is confirmed safe.

Health officials have sampled schools in the province but discovered no other cases of infection.

