[3] New Zealand: H3N2
Date: Thu 21 Jun 2012
Source: NewstalkZB [edited]
http://www.newstalkzb.co.nz/auckland/news/nbhea/769331892-Spike-in-cases-of-dangerous-strain-of-flu


There's been a noticeable spike in the number of influenza cases among New Zealanders in recent weeks. Latest data show the influenza strain A/H3N2 has been most predominant in Auckland and South Canterbury.

Virus expert and National Influenza Specialist Group spokesperson Dr Lance Jennings says the predominance of the H3N2 virus is a major concern. He says infections with this virus can be particularly severe for the elderly, and those with an ongoing medical condition.

Dr Jennings says a major outbreak of H3N2 would cause a surge in hospital admissions and deaths.

[Byline: Juliette Sivertsen]

